rComments: Not sure if he really wants to teach anyone or just want to show off. Essentially lectures are designed in such a way that you will be exposed to something, but in a fairly non-mathematically rigorous way so that you cannot generalize those concepts, manipulate the math behind it, or really get to the crux of it. Need to really think about teaching

I hate to say this, but David is an awful teacher. His lectures are just like seminars at a PhD or Post-doc level. If you are already an expert like he is, then you will enjoy his lectures. If you are a student, his lectures are useless. You will most likely understand only 10 mins of his 3-hour lecture every week. Avoid him if possible.
He is smart but not very informative. He seems talk to himself instead of teaching student
